  <title>Introduction</title>

  <para>Peergreen web console is a Vaadin based modular application. There is
  two editions for Peergreen web console : <emphasis
  role="bold">community</emphasis> and <emphasis
  role="bold">professional</emphasis>.</para>

  <section>
    <title>Community Edition</title>

    <para>Community edition targets developers. It allows to create instances
    of web console with or without authentication (development mode). Users
    can develop extensions and contribute to the web console.</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Professional Edition</title>

    <para>Professional edition is installed in professional edition of
    Peergreen Server. It allows to instantiate a secured web console and can
    not coexits with Community Edition in the same server.</para>
  </section>

